{"type":"message","id":"4f9343da","parentId":"e2c53c5a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:32:45.660Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q4nzwx3kwpav_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: workflows\ndescription: Use when user asks to execute, find, or run pre-built VibeSurf automation workflows like video downloads, auto-login, or data collection templates.\n---\n\n# Workflows - Pre-Built Automations\n\n## Overview\n\nExecute pre-configured VibeSurf workflows for common automation tasks.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- You know a workflow exists for your task\n- You want reusable automation sequences\n- Task has a known pattern (video download, auto-login, etc.)\n\n**Examples:**\n- Video download workflows\n- Auto-login sequences\n- Data collection templates\n- Social media posting\n\n## Available Actions\n\n| Action | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `search_workflows` | Find workflows by keyword |\n| `get_workflow_params` | See required parameters |\n| `execute_workflow` | Run with custom values |\n\n## The Pattern\n\n1. **Search** for workflow with keyword\n2. **Check** parameters required\n3. **Execute** with tweak parameters (custom values)\n\n## Tweak Parameters\n\nWorkflows have adjustable components called \"tweaks\". Provide custom values to customize workflow behavior without modifying the workflow itself.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n| Practice | Why |\n|----------|-----|\n| Search before executing | Confirm workflow exists and see parameters |\n| Use tweaks for customization | Don't modify workflow directly |\n| Check results | Returns file paths and detailed output |\n\n## Common Workflow Types\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| Video Download | Download from YouTube, etc. |\n| Auto-Login | Authenticate to sites |\n| Data Collection | Scrape structured data |\n| Social Post | Post to platforms |\n\n## Workflow vs Browser-Use\n\n| Factor | Workflows | Browser-Use |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| Reusability | Pre-built, reusable | Custom, one-off |\n| Setup | None (already exists) | Describe task each time |\n| Use when | Known pattern exists | Custom automation needed |\n\n**Decision:** Known pattern → workflows. Unique task → browser-use.\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error | Solution |\n|-------|----------|\n| Workflow not found | Use `search_workflows` to find correct ID |\n| Invalid tweak params | Check `get_workflow_params` for correct IDs |\n| Execution failed | Verify all required params provided |\n\n## Finding Workflows\n\nCommon search keywords:\n- `video download`, `youtube`\n- `auto login`\n- `data collection`, `scrape`\n- `social media`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776065565659}}
{"type":"message","id":"5888c97f","parentId":"4f9343da","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:33:09.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing me to https://clawhub.1688.com/ which seems to be a skill marketplace for 1688. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The URL `clawhub.1688.com` suggests this might be a skill specifically for 1688\n2. ClawHub is the skill marketplace I saw in my available skills list\n3. But the domain seems odd - 1688.com domain for a skill marketplace? That seems suspicious.\n\nWait, looking at the original skill listing:\n- `clawhub` skill at `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md`\n\nThe user mentioned \"clawhub.1688.com\" - but clawhub.ai is the skill marketplace. This could be a typo or the user is confused. Let me check if this is actually ClawHub (clawhub.ai) or something else.\n\n\nThe domain clawhub.1688.com doesn't seem right - ClawHub's actual marketplace is at clawhub.ai, so this might be a misunderstanding on the user's part or they're referring to something specific to their setup.\n\nRegardless, they've confirmed they want to go with VibeSurf for browser-based workflows, and they're asking whether we can create a reusable VibeSurf workflow for our product selection process in Vietnam market. That's actually a solid idea - we could optimize the SOP into a VibeSurf workflow that would let us run this repeatedly and scale it up.\n\nSo the approach would be to first validate the entire flow manually with VibeSurf browser commands, then consolidate those steps into a single workflow definition, and finally scale it up by running multiple product lookups in parallel. I should acknowledge their thinking and explain how we can move forward with this plan."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 明白了！你的思路非常正确：\n\n---\n\n## VibeSurf Workflow 的价值\n\n| 维度 | 没有 Workflow | 有 Workflow |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| **每次执行** | 重新描述整个流程 | 一键启动 |\n| **Token 消耗** | 每次都重新规划步骤 | 只描述输入/输出 |\n| **操作效率** | 人工触发多步 | 自动串联 |\n| **Scale** | 单个商品 | 批量商品列表 |\n| **迭代优化** | 每次都要人工确认 | 优化一次，批量生效 |\n\n---\n\n## 实施路径\n\n```\n第一步（现在）：手动跑通最小闭环\n    ↓\n第二步：把 SOP 固化成 VibeSurf Workflow\n    ↓\n第三步：Scale — 输入商品列表，批量执行\n```\n\n---\n\n## 关于 clawhub.1688.com\n\n我访问不了这个地址（被拦截）。但如果这是 1688 官方的 Skill 市场，你可以截图给我看看具体是什么功能？或者直接告诉我 Skill 的名字，我帮你查一下是否能用。\n\n---\n\n## 下一步\n\n要我现在就开始**第一步：手动跑通最小闭环**吗？\n\n给我一个 1688 商品链接 or 越南 TK 商品链接，我用 VibeSurf 演示抓取 → 评分 → 写入 Bitable 的完整流程。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776065565660,"responseId":"062bcf1db030ea4de93186391089b0e9"}}
