{"type":"message","id":"82d23bcd","parentId":"09c1ec33","timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:00:58.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that the browser (VibeSurf) has good stealth/privacy features and they're using it because it supports workflows, skills, MCP, model access, and can be controlled by AI at scale. They're confused about why it's hanging when we try to use it.\n\nLooking at the last browser state output, I can see the page loaded successfully - we can see the TikTok Seller Center sidebar with menu items like \"商品卡\", \"热门\", \"商品卡畅销商品\" etc. But the issue seems to be that when we try to extract data, the API calls are hanging.\n\nLet me try a more targeted approach - since the page has loaded, let me try to extract data with a simpler method or take a screenshot to see what's actually displayed on the page.\n\nActually, the user mentioned \"agent browser\" is not working - they might be referring to the browser-use agent approach which was hanging earlier. They seem to prefer the direct browser control approach.\n\nLet me try to click on \"商品卡畅销商品\" (Top Selling Products) menu item to navigate to that page and see the actual product data."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 理解你的痛点。VibeSurf 本身功能是完整的，支持 workflow、skill、MCP、模型接入、scale 控制 —— 架构没问题。\n\n问题出在 **browser-use agent**（自动规划路径的那种）容易卡住，但**直接精确控制**是可以用的。\n\n看页面已经加载成功了，左侧有\"商品卡畅销商品\"菜单。让我点击进入：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_548a7y5feq2j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:9335/api/tool/execute \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"action_name\":\"browser.click\",\"parameters\":{\"index\":8948}}'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067244740,"responseId":"0