{"type":"message","id":"8b2db724","parentId":"e8e58114","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:44:38.730Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System (untrusted): [2026-04-13 16:56:28 GMT+8] Exec failed (good-kel, signal SIGTERM)\nSystem (untrusted): [2026-04-13 16:57:17 GMT+8] Exec failed (vivid-or, signal SIGTERM)\nSystem: [2026-04-13 17:43:33 GMT+8] Feishu[tts] DM | ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 [msg:om_x100b52ffe28d84b4c34f08aac3b1edd]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52ffe28d84b4c34f08aac3b1edd\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-13 17:43 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```\n\n那VibeSurf的这个后台用的就是Chrome 142这个版本啊。\n\n那我们在普通电脑上登录是没有问题的，会是因为性能问题导致的吗？"}],"timestamp":1776073478724}}
{"type":"message","id":"66a49c5f","parentId":"8b2db724","timestamp":"2026-04-13T09:45:01.512Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the VibeSurf issue might be due to performance - they're saying VibeSurf uses Chrome 142, and they can login fine on a regular computer. They're wondering if it's a performance issue causing the browser to freeze when loading the heavy TikTok Seller pages.\n\nThis is a good question. Let me think about this:\n\n1. Chrome 142 is a recent version, so that's not the issue\n2. The fact that they can login fine on a regular computer suggests it's not a captcha or anti-bot issue\n3. The TikTok Seller Center pages are notoriously heavy (React apps with lots of components)\n4. VibeSurf might be running with limited resources or in a container/VM environment\n\nThe issue is likely:\n- Resource constraints on the server where VibeSurf is running\n- Memory limits causing Chrome to freeze on heavy pages\n- Network latency causing timeouts\n\nLet me try to check the browser state again and see if we can diagnose further. But first I should ask if VibeSurf is running locally on their machine or on a server, as that would help diagnose the performance issue."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 很有可能是这个原因！\n\n**VibeSurf 运行方式：**\n- 如果是 **本地 Mac/PC** → 资源充足，应该没问题\n- 如果是 **服务器/容器** → 内存和 CPU 限制，heavy page 容易卡死\n\n---\n\n## 排查建议\n\n1. **VibeSurf 是在你本机跑的吗？** 还是在云服务器上？\n\n2. **本地试一下**：在你本地浏览器（Chrome）直接打开 TK 后台，看是否很快？\n\n3. **如果是服务器部署**：可以尝试增加 VibeSurf 的资源配置（内存、CPU）\n\n---\n\n先确认一下运行环境，我再帮你想具体解决方案。你本机是 Mac 还是 Windows？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776073478730,"responseId":"062bee074c1393d73f1a34a58d461995"}}
